<div id="review_3653521297" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3653521297" />
    <a title="Henry" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/63028700-henry"><img alt="Henry" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1562101030p2/63028700.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3653521297?book_show_action=true">Nov 28, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Henry" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Henry" href="/user/show/63028700-henry">Henry</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3653521297" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6542008651756188963">A classic post-apocalyptic novel written in 1959. I cannot believe I never read this novel before! This book along with Nevil Shute&apos;s &quot;On the Beach&quot; (written a couple of years earlier) and Walter Miller&apos;s &quot;A Canticle for Leibowitz&quot; also written in 1959, form a trio of unforgettable post nuclear war classics. Extremely highly recommended. I would also note that although all three are certainly written for adults, they are very suitable reading for anyone over eleven or twelve years old. I am reco</span>
  <span id="freeText6542008651756188963" style="display:none">A classic post-apocalyptic novel written in 1959. I cannot believe I never read this novel before! This book along with Nevil Shute's "On the Beach" (written a couple of years earlier) and Walter Miller's "A Canticle for Leibowitz" also written in 1959, form a trio of unforgettable post nuclear war classics. Extremely highly recommended. I would also note that although all three are certainly written for adults, they are very suitable reading for anyone over eleven or twelve years old. I am recommending them highly to my grandchildren in that age group.</span>
  <a data-text-id="6542008651756188963" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


